   Date: Mon, 12 Sep 88 10:24:24 PDT
   From: Peter Karp &lt;KARP@SUMEX-AIM.Stanford.EDU&gt;

   Sorry if I'm missing something, but if you were to mail to
   TCp-IP@mail.list, how would the domain system know which of hundreds
   of MX records to use?  MX records are not selected based on the
   recipient field.  Wouldn't you have to mail to something like
   TCP-IP@tcp-ip.list ?  The domain  tcp-ip.list  would have an MX
   pointing to  sri-nic.arpa .

   Peter
   -------


Exactly right - that's what I get for not paying attention to how the
system works.  Mike

